text:
Oh, geez. I really can't tell you how happy I am to hear you talk about being more comfortable streaming for us, Gura. You being you is always so hilarious, sweet, exciting, and inspiring, and you deserve to feel at ease when you work so hard to entertain us. I really hope that feeling continues to grow for you; it's only up from here, little shark, and I can't wait to see where the future takes us all together~

And thanks for much for spending this time with us today. I never get too bothered by being alone for Valentine's Day, but these streams really made the day feel special instead of just plain. I hope being with us made you feel like you weren't alone today, either. You may be kinda ya be, or a tiny bit strange sometimes, but you really are the most precious little goofball in the world, and you should never have to feel lonely in this big, scary world. Love you, Gura; see you tomorrow for more fun times <3

(Also, this is heckin random, but if it matters, I personally really like the idea of watching vegan/vegetarian cooking streams. My brother lets me try a lot of the vegan foods he makes, and I've always found it really fascinating how much you can do with them. So if you've ever felt like doing things like that again, please do!)
